race.comment: BRAVE WASP (4) resumes and two back was beaten a whisker in an Open 3 at Belmont. Was backed off the map there following, and pulled up with an issue. He's just missed in town at both fresh runs and will be naturally improved. Has Faithfull aboard and just needs average luck from the wide gate to return a winner. ZALI'S GIFT (13) was disappointing two back at Belmont, but her metro form around that reads well. Keeps Fiore and should be right in the finish. LADY COCO (5) led and was nudged out at Bunbury three back, and resumed here 12 days ago and needed the outing. She's placed 5/7 here and goes second-up. She has to skip over from an outside gate, but Galati replaces the 3kg apprentice, and he's currently striking at 24%. CALATHINITE (7) comes out of the same race, placing behind a dominant winner. He's still learning but will use an inside barrier and is sure to give a sight.
